# Testing Rules

## Mock Data

- Located in `src/test/mocks/`
- Realistic, representative data
- Cover edge cases
- Type-safe (match schema types)

```typescript
// Good mock data
export const mockParsedResume: ParsedResume = {
  personal: {
    name: 'Alex Johnson',
    email: 'alex@example.com',
    // ... complete object
  },
  // ...
};
```

## Test Structure

```typescript
describe('ComponentName', () => {
  it('renders correctly with default props', () => {
    // Arrange
    const props = { ... };
    
    // Act
    render(<Component {...props} />);
    
    // Assert
    expect(screen.getByText('...')).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
```

## What to Test

### Unit Tests
- Utility functions
- Zod schemas (valid/invalid inputs)
- Custom hooks

### Component Tests
- Renders with various props
- User interactions
- Accessibility

### Integration Tests
- API routes
- Full features

## What Not to Test
- Third-party libraries
- Implementation details
- Styles/CSS
